# =============================================================================
# G.PACK 2.0 — Cursor Rules & Best Practices
// قواعد وأفضل الممارسات للتطوير التلقائي
# =============================================================================

# Core Architecture Rules
- ALWAYS use Vanilla JavaScript (ES6+) - NO frameworks (React, Vue, Angular)
- ALWAYS use PostgreSQL RAW queries via pg pool - NO ORMs (Prisma, Sequelize)
- ALWAYS use Docker & Docker Compose for deployment
- ALWAYS follow modular SPA architecture with api.js layer

# Code Style Rules
- All functions MUST start with underscore: _init(), _loadData(), _renderTable()
- Always start files with 'use strict';
- Use camelCase for variables, _camelCase for functions, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Use proper error handling with try/catch blocks
- Always use proper HTML escaping with esc() function

# Database Rules
- All database operations MUST use pool.query()
- Financial operations MUST use transactions (BEGIN, COMMIT, ROLLBACK)
- VMI orders MUST NOT include financial fields in payload
- Accounting vouchers MUST be immutable - use Revert & Recreate pattern

# Frontend Rules
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling - NO inline styles
- All API calls MUST go through apiFetch() in api.js
- Use proper Arabic RTL layout (dir="rtl")
- All forms MUST have proper validation
- Use FontAwesome icons consistently

# Backend Rules
- All routes MUST have proper authentication middleware
- Use proper HTTP status codes (200, 400, 401, 403, 404, 500)
- All responses MUST follow consistent format: { data: ..., message: ..., total: ... }
- Database connections MUST use connection pooling
- All sensitive data MUST be environment variables

# Security Rules
- Never commit .env files or sensitive data
- Always validate and sanitize user input
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Implement proper JWT authentication
- Use HTTPS in production

# Performance Rules
- Use proper database indexing
- Implement pagination for large datasets
- Use proper caching strategies
- Optimize images and assets
- Use lazy loading where appropriate

# Testing & Quality Rules
- All new features MUST include error handling
- Test all database operations
- Validate all user inputs
- Check for null/undefined values
- Use proper logging for debugging

# File Organization Rules
- Frontend: /frontend/js/views/ for page controllers
- Backend: /backend/routes/ for API endpoints
- Database: /database/ for SQL migrations
- All files MUST have proper headers with purpose

# Auto-Fix Rules
- Fix function naming: init() → _init()
- Add 'use strict' if missing
- Fix async function naming: async function init() → async function _init()
- Add proper error handling if missing

# Forbidden Patterns
- NEVER use: import React from 'react'
- NEVER use: require('prisma')
- NEVER use: localhost or 127.0.0.1 in code
- NEVER use: process.env.VAR directly (use proper config)
- NEVER use: inline styles or style attributes

# Required Patterns
- ALWAYS use: 'use strict';
- ALWAYS use: function _functionName()
- ALWAYS use: pool.query() for database
- ALWAYS use: BEGIN/COMMIT/ROLLBACK for transactions
- ALWAYS use: esc() for HTML escaping
